beer.beer_description:
Our first seasonal brew is a big & bold Red IPA named after an old tree stump tattooed with
an evil eye, once located on Lake George just outside the Capital. With a forward hop profile,
it’s full bodied, packed with flavour and aroma and has a balanced dry finish. We’ve used
fresh Batlow grown US Cascade hops for extra
hop kick. Best enjoyed in season.

Hops: Columbus, Simcoe, Pacifica,
Southern Cross, Montueka, US Cascade
